       <div class="paragraph-group"> 
        <h2> How Does AdMob Work </h2> 
        <p> AdMob can be used for Android and iOS apps. AdMob allows developers to monetize their app(s) by displaying in-app ads from other advertisers. </p> 
        <p> You can set filters to ensure the ads being displayed are relevant to your app users. You also have control over the types of ad formats you allow. Choose from banner ads, full pages interstitials, video ads, and native ads. </p> 
        <p> AdMob also offers a comprehensive mediation platforms which allows developers to manage and mediate ad requests out to more than 40 third-party network. This helps to maximize your app monetization. </p> 
        <h2> How is AdMob different from AdWords </h2> 
        <p> You can use AdWords to create <a href="https://support.google.com/adwords/answer/6309936?hl=en" target="_blank">app install</a> campaigns that display to users on apps within the AdMob network. Connecting your AdWords and AdMob accounts allows you to optimize your advertising experience. With AdWords, you can create <a href="https://support.google.com/adwords/answer/6247380?hl=en" target="_blank">universal app campaigns</a> to advertise your app across Google Search and Google Play, YouTube, the Google Display Network, AdMob and more. Once you achieve more app installs, you can then use AdMob to show ads in your app and monetize users. </p> 
       </div>
       <!--[if !IE]> --> 
       <picture class="icon">
        <source sizes="(max-width: 768px) 200px, (max-width: 1024px) 200px, 200px" srcset="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/Sz8uo3eNkEba7oPpuH4FTsDf4ntWBpujZbKGSGSK9BFOjEJSoLJdrWB1Moi9-MsWj6xENiIuJkXs9KdypDqiAwECktr3E9yfyR9F=w0 344w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/uEncw5dAfQ2NXdtREA7_2UHTQ1m_anDz7zcscVnnVQnOPA71JSRZtBrp0AAcaofK_v34lVpauX4FqPJE2Vn4kz5bWK4xjlVxFIxLcA=w0 200w"> 
